1. 1. T. Pomponius ‘'Atticus, a Roman of good family, was born in 109 Β. c. He removed to Athens in 88, where he resided for twenty- three years. He then returned to' Rome, and lived the life ofa man of literary tastes and habits. He avoided politics and a military career. He was an intimate friend of many prominent people of his time, among whom were Cicero, Nepos, Antony, and Brutus. At- ticus stands as the best type of a Roman gentlemen of culture and retirement. He acquired the cognomen Atticus, ‘⁴ the Attican,'' from his long residence in Athens. He died in 32 Β. e.
